00:53:31,167 --> 00:53:34,545
But they grilled the meat for us.
I can't even grab it for you?

752
00:53:34,629 --> 00:53:38,591
Oh, this is too much. Seriously.
You should've been nice to me sooner.

753
00:53:38,674 --> 00:53:43,137
Then how am I supposed
to thank Assistant Manager Lee Kyeong-do?

754
00:53:44,889 --> 00:53:45,890
Okay.

755
00:53:49,143 --> 00:53:50,394
Is it good?

756
00:53:50,478 --> 00:53:51,312
Totally.

757
00:54:00,738 --> 00:54:05,159
So? Is Seo Ji-woo going to England
or something?

758
00:54:07,411 --> 00:54:12,458
Oh, whatever. It's over now. The end.

759
00:54:13,084 --> 00:54:14,085
Okay.

760
00:54:15,002 --> 00:54:18,464
My forever rival Seo Ji-woo is out now.

761
00:54:18,547 --> 00:54:20,466
It's up to me now.

762
00:54:23,469 --> 00:54:26,555
Why is Seo Ji-woo Jin Han-kyeong's rival?

763
00:54:26,639 --> 00:54:30,434
Hey, it's been 10 years
since I've been asking you out.

764
00:54:30,518 --> 00:54:32,353
That's why she's my enemy.

765
00:54:32,436 --> 00:54:34,939
You're cutting me off
because you couldn't move on.

766
00:54:36,107 --> 00:54:39,694
"Date me and I'll buy you a car."
"Date me and I'll fund your lease."

767
00:54:39,777 --> 00:54:44,824
"I got the Louis collaboration sneakers.
If you date me, they're yours."

768
00:54:44,907 --> 00:54:46,450
You call that asking me out?

769
00:54:46,534 --> 00:54:48,244
I was asking you out.

770
00:54:49,662 --> 00:54:51,914
Good. I like how you're consistent.

771
00:54:52,581 --> 00:54:54,375
Hold on. I have something to show you.

772
00:54:55,584 --> 00:54:56,585
You sound determined.

773
00:54:56,669 --> 00:54:58,671
Ta-da.

774
00:54:59,964 --> 00:55:01,674
I bought a house in Oksu-dong.

775
00:55:04,885 --> 00:55:08,222
Have you seen anyone
buying a house without a mortgage?

776
00:55:08,305 --> 00:55:10,599
Look. That's me.

777
00:55:12,685 --> 00:55:13,519
You're showing off.

778
00:55:13,602 --> 00:55:16,897
Why do you think I'm showing off?
You should move in with me.

779
00:55:16,981 --> 00:55:18,315
Oh, really?

780
00:55:20,109 --> 00:55:22,528
Oh, don't call your mother already.

781
00:55:22,611 --> 00:55:23,487
Come on.

782
00:55:23,571 --> 00:55:25,156
Why are you so hasty?

783
00:55:25,239 --> 00:55:26,699
Still, I should tell her.

784
00:55:28,117 --> 00:55:29,535
- Here, press it.
- Already…

785
00:55:30,995 --> 00:55:32,663
Did that not work?

786
00:55:33,539 --> 00:55:36,375
Jeez, so cheap. Seriously, so cheap.

787
00:55:36,459 --> 00:55:38,502
- Would you move in if it's Apgujeong?
- So call them.

788
00:55:38,586 --> 00:55:40,212
Put that away. Damn it.

789
00:55:43,632 --> 00:55:46,552
Good job. I know that was hard.

790
00:55:47,678 --> 00:55:50,222
So don't say
you want to go for round two after this.

791
00:55:50,306 --> 00:55:52,141
I'm having ice cream.

792
00:55:52,224 --> 00:55:54,560
Seriously, enough with the ice cream.

793
00:55:57,980 --> 00:55:58,981
Hello?

794
00:55:59,857 --> 00:56:00,858
Yes.

795
00:56:02,276 --> 00:56:04,528
What? Where?

796
00:56:22,922 --> 00:56:23,923
That was fast.

797
00:56:24,465 --> 00:56:25,424
Nice to meet you.

798
00:56:25,966 --> 00:56:27,301
This isn't the first time we've met.

799
00:56:28,636 --> 00:56:32,098
We met when you were working
at a hotel buffet in college.

800
00:56:35,017 --> 00:56:36,018
I see.

801
00:56:37,853 --> 00:56:39,021
Anyway, what brings you here?

802
00:56:40,481 --> 00:56:42,566
I wanted to meet you as soon as possible,

803
00:56:42,650 --> 00:56:46,112
and if I came here,
I thought you'd come as fast as you could.

804
00:56:47,404 --> 00:56:48,948
Is it about the article today?

805
00:56:49,031 --> 00:56:52,493
That too, and I have a favor to ask you.

806
00:56:57,414 --> 00:56:59,792
The article about Ji-woo's ex-husband.

807
00:56:59,875 --> 00:57:04,255
Ji-woo already thanked me for that.
Why did you want to see me?

808
00:57:04,338 --> 00:57:05,840
A picture of you two was taken.

809
00:57:05,923 --> 00:57:08,300
Yes, to explain that--

810
00:57:08,384 --> 00:57:09,593
I took it.

811
00:57:12,555 --> 00:57:15,474
I didn't take it myself. I paid someone.

812
00:57:15,558 --> 00:57:18,769
Anyway, I reported it.

813
00:57:30,114 --> 00:57:31,115
Why?

814
00:57:32,324 --> 00:57:34,535
To tie Ji-woo down.

815
00:57:34,618 --> 00:57:35,494
What?

816
00:57:35,578 --> 00:57:38,330
You heard
Ji-woo's going to England, right?

817
00:57:39,039 --> 00:57:44,211
If she leaves now,
she'll have no standing.

818
00:57:44,295 --> 00:57:46,964
If she leaves now,
she'll have no standing.

819
00:57:47,047 --> 00:57:50,092
And you're the only person
who can stop her.

820
00:57:55,014 --> 00:57:58,934
I don't know what you're talking about.

821
00:57:59,018 --> 00:58:01,854
Ji-woo needs to return to the company.

822
00:58:03,480 --> 00:58:07,693
Ji-woo will run JARIM Apparel
better than me.

823
00:58:07,776 --> 00:58:09,653
You saw the article today, right?

824
00:58:09,737 --> 00:58:12,573
The two-piece set that Ji-woo wore
sold out immediately.

825
00:58:14,408 --> 00:58:18,078
Ji-woo is better at fashion than I am.

826
00:58:27,796 --> 00:58:30,090
Well then. I had a long day today.

827
00:58:30,174 --> 00:58:31,800
Stop Ji-woo.

828
00:58:34,803 --> 00:58:39,099
Why are you doing this, really?
There's nothing between me and her.

829
00:58:41,185 --> 00:58:42,645
Really?

830
00:58:46,148 --> 00:58:51,028
Were you 28? You and Ji-woo.

831
00:58:51,111 --> 00:58:51,946
Look.

832
00:58:52,029 --> 00:58:55,449
After Ji-woo left
and your father's treatment was over,

833
00:58:55,532 --> 00:58:57,243
you spent a year drunk.

834
00:59:00,120 --> 00:59:05,751
There should be nothing between you two,
but you could still worry about her.

835
00:59:06,877 --> 00:59:07,878
Jeez.

836
00:59:08,879 --> 00:59:11,590
What are you pulling at? Huh?

837
00:59:11,674 --> 00:59:14,009
Seo Ji-woo and Seo Ji-yeon.
What are you two women doing?

838
00:59:14,093 --> 00:59:17,888
Our mom is not a good mom.

839
00:59:17,972 --> 00:59:20,307
Not to mention that my husband is worse.

840
00:59:20,391 --> 00:59:22,977
So what does that have to do with me?

841
00:59:24,645 --> 00:59:28,607
Ji-woo will become penniless.

842
00:59:29,191 --> 00:59:33,487
If she leaves now...
In a year or two years...

843
00:59:34,697 --> 00:59:36,198
Ji-woo…

844
00:59:38,909 --> 00:59:43,038
Ji-woo will be a beggar.

845
00:59:45,374 --> 00:59:48,961
My mom is powerless,
and my husband is not a good man.

846
00:59:49,044 --> 00:59:51,588
I'm the only one who can protect Ji-woo.

847
00:59:54,133 --> 00:59:55,467
But I'm…

848
00:59:57,511 --> 01:00:00,222
I'm losing my memories.

849
01:00:04,184 --> 01:00:07,604
I have Alzheimer's.

850
01:00:14,236 --> 01:00:17,781
<i>Divorce isn't the best option.</i>

851
01:00:17,865 --> 01:00:20,868
<i>It'll take a long time,</i>
<i>and my chances of winning aren't high.</i>

852
01:00:21,535 --> 01:00:25,748
If I become blank before that,
my husband will sell the company.

853
01:00:28,334 --> 01:00:32,796
<i>I can't explain everything,</i>
<i>why Ji-woo's likely to become penniless.</i>

854
01:00:34,798 --> 01:00:37,718
JARIM APPAREL

855
01:00:39,636 --> 01:00:46,602
The only way is for JARIM Apparel
to become Seo Ji-woo's company.

856
01:01:06,497 --> 01:01:08,832
<i>My dad and I</i>
<i>are the first generation of JARIM.</i>

857
01:01:08,916 --> 01:01:12,336
And Ji-woo has more than enough
to become the second generation of JARIM.

858
01:01:18,384 --> 01:01:20,177
<i>Please stop Ji-woo.</i>

859
01:01:21,470 --> 01:01:22,471
Next person in line.

860
01:01:22,554 --> 01:01:27,309
<i>If you don't want to talk about old love,</i>
<i>can you do it for your friendship?</i>

861
01:01:27,976 --> 01:01:32,147
Hello. Can you show me
your ticket and your passport? Okay.

862
01:01:35,109 --> 01:01:36,777
Do you have any luggage?

863
01:01:36,860 --> 01:01:37,694
Yes.

864
01:01:37,778 --> 01:01:38,737
Can you put it up here?

865
01:01:40,697 --> 01:01:41,782
Let's talk.

866
01:01:41,865 --> 01:01:42,908
Are you crazy?

867
01:01:45,411 --> 01:01:48,247
First of all, since you're here,
put it up here. It's heavy.

868
01:01:48,330 --> 01:01:49,498
Let's talk.

869
01:01:49,581 --> 01:01:50,916
I have to get on board.

870
01:01:50,999 --> 01:01:51,834
Take the next one.

871
01:01:51,917 --> 01:01:53,252
This isn't KTX.

872
01:01:56,422 --> 01:01:59,133
Sorry about that.
Hey, put it up here first. No, put…

873
01:02:00,676 --> 01:02:03,178
Can I have my passport back?
Sorry, I'll be right back.

874
01:02:03,262 --> 01:02:04,680
That crazy bastard…

875
01:02:06,682 --> 01:02:07,975
Hey, Lee Kyeong-do. Hey!

876
01:02:08,058 --> 01:02:11,228
What the heck is wrong with him?
This is crazy.

877
01:02:16,191 --> 01:02:19,361
Hey, Lee Kyeong-do. Stop right there. Hey!

878
01:02:22,406 --> 01:02:23,532
Oh, seriously.

879
01:02:26,785 --> 01:02:27,619
Jeez.

880
01:02:32,666 --> 01:02:36,837
Oh, sir! Stop him. That guy.
Catch him. Hurry!

881
01:02:38,630 --> 01:02:40,090
Sir, can we have a moment?

882
01:02:40,174 --> 01:02:42,301
Yes. We know each other.

883
01:02:43,635 --> 01:02:44,636
Mom?

884
01:02:45,262 --> 01:02:46,096
Catch him.

885
01:02:46,180 --> 01:02:48,932
- Wait, wait. I'm not a bad guy.
- Let's talk over there.

886
01:02:49,016 --> 01:02:50,767
Come with us.

887
01:02:51,768 --> 01:02:52,936
Wait.

888
01:03:00,319 --> 01:03:04,239
SURELY TOMORROW

889
01:03:05,157 --> 01:03:06,533
I thought it was a color film.

890
01:03:06,617 --> 01:03:08,452
Black and white makes it look cool.

891
01:03:08,535 --> 01:03:09,703
Say it again to Ji-woo's face.

892
01:03:09,786 --> 01:03:11,872
Our matching items aren't visible.

893
01:03:11,955 --> 01:03:13,415
It's not visible!

894
01:03:13,499 --> 01:03:17,753
Why's this a big deal?
Shouldn't have brought the camera. Shit.

895
01:03:17,836 --> 01:03:20,005
I feel black and white.
Let's grab a drink.

896
01:03:20,088 --> 01:03:21,924
Sure, it's on, black and white Jeong-min.

897
01:03:22,007 --> 01:03:25,260
I developed it too.
Don't you have a sense of shame?

898
01:03:28,388 --> 01:03:29,223
Ji-woo.

899
01:03:30,891 --> 01:03:33,060
You look pretty
because it's black and white.

900
01:03:33,143 --> 01:03:34,645
You want a punch in the face?

901
01:03:34,728 --> 01:03:36,438
Let's go. Come on. Let's go.

902
01:03:36,522 --> 01:03:39,441
Kyeong-do. Kyeong-do?

903
01:04:20,816 --> 01:04:24,194
I turned off the gas valve. I ran out of
underwear, so I took one of yours.

904
01:04:25,195 --> 01:04:27,197
No questions, please.

905
01:04:27,281 --> 01:04:28,949
<i>Is running away your specialty?</i>

906
01:04:30,242 --> 01:04:31,994
Did you get on top of him?

907
01:04:32,077 --> 01:04:35,455
<i>I just pulled a prank</i>
<i>to see what he's like.</i>

908
01:04:36,290 --> 01:04:38,500
<i>Do you really like me?</i>

909
01:04:39,543 --> 01:04:42,004
You never blame me even a little.
That pisses me off even more.

910
01:04:42,087 --> 01:04:43,380
What do you want me to do then?

911
01:04:45,841 --> 01:04:48,760
<i>There should be a thesis about you two.</i>
<i>You guys are weird.</i>

912
01:04:49,595 --> 01:04:53,390
<i>I went when I was 20</i>
<i>and when I was 28. I'm worried.</i>

913
01:04:53,473 --> 01:04:54,391
Is it love?
